# Globs — filename patterns

A **glob** is a wildcard the **shell** expands into matching filenames **before** the command runs. `ls *.txt` → `ls a.txt b.txt …` — `ls` never sees the `*`.

## The patterns

- **`*`** — any run of chars (not a leading `.`)
- **`?`** — exactly one char
- **`[abc]`** / **`[a-z]`** — one char, set / range
- **`[!abc]`** — one char, **not** those

`report?.csv` → `report1.csv`, not `report10.csv`.

## Two traps

- The **shell** expands globs, **not** the command
- **No match → the literal pattern passes through** (`ls *.none` errors) — `shopt -s nullglob` to fix

⚠️ **Globs are NOT regex.** Glob `*` = any chars; regex `*` = zero-or-more of the previous. (Regex → module 04.)
